# Tabby marketing site (`website/`)

Static landing page for Tabby. **Separate** from the Chrome extension build; do not mix WXT and website dependencies.

## Published URL

**https://yanovian.github.io/chrome-ext-tabby/**

This is the **shortest** GitHub Pages URL for repo `yanovian/chrome-ext-tabby`: one path segment (`chrome-ext-tabby`), no `/website/` suffix. The site source lives in `website/` but deploys to the repo root on Pages.

Do not add a custom domain or rename the extension repo in docs or config.

## Base path

- Production / preview: `VITE_BASE_PATH=/chrome-ext-tabby/` (see `website/.env.production`)
- Local dev (`make website-dev`): base `/` for simpler localhost URLs
- CI: `VITE_BASE_PATH=/${{ github.event.repository.name }}/` in `.github/workflows/pages.yml`

Keep these aligned. If the GitHub repo name ever changed, update `.env.production`, `Makefile` `GITHUB_PAGES_BASE`, and README links together.

## Local commands

Prefer **Makefile** from repo root:

| Command | Purpose |
|---------|---------|
| `make website-install` | `pnpm install` in `website/` |
| `make website-dev` | Hot reload at `http://localhost:5173/` |
| `make website-build` | Production build to `website/dist/` |
| `make website-preview` | Build + preview at `http://localhost:4173/chrome-ext-tabby/` |
| `make website-clean` | Remove `website/dist/` and generated `website/public/` |
| `make website-lint-i18n` | Check locale JSON keys match `en/` (no missing, no extra) |
| `make website-lint-i18n-fix` | Add missing keys as `""` in other locales (prints warnings) |

Equivalent: `cd website && pnpm dev|build|preview`.

## Assets

Icons, GIFs, and **Lottie JSON** are not duplicated in git. `website/scripts/copy-assets.mjs` copies from extension `public/` and `lottie-json/` on `predev` and `prebuild`.

- **Marketing animations:** use Lottie via `TabbyLottie` (`@lottiefiles/dotlottie-web`, canvas). Tabby JSON is authored for DotLottie, not `lottie-web`.
- **SEO / sharing:** `@unhead/react` + `@unhead/schema-org` in `Seo.tsx` / `PageSeo.tsx` (i18n via `react-i18next`). English strings in `src/locales/en/seo.json`. `vite-plugin-html` injects the same English meta into `index.html` for crawlers that skip JS. `build-og-image.mjs` writes `og-image.png`. `static/robots.txt` and `static/sitemap.xml` copy into `public/`.
- **i18n:** committed JSON in `website/src/locales/<locale>/` (38 languages, same set as the Chrome Web Store). `website/src/i18n/locales.ts` lists codes, native labels, and RTL (`ar`, `fa`). Language picker in the top bar; choice saved in `localStorage`. Legal page body stays English (`PRIVACY.md` / `TERMS.md`); UI chrome is translated. Vite bundles these files via `import.meta.glob` (shipped in the production JS). **No locale generators.** Edit JSON by hand.

After changing `src/locales/en/`:

1. `cd website && pnpm lint-i18n-fix` to add empty keys to other locales (warns which locale/key).
2. Fill translations in each locale folder.
3. `cd website && pnpm lint-i18n` (also runs before `pnpm build` / `make website-build`).

`lint-i18n` fails if any locale has missing or extra keys compared to `en`.

After changing extension GIFs, icons, or Lottie source clips, rebuild or restart dev so the site picks them up.

## Extension repo isolation

- `website/` has its own `package.json` and `pnpm-lock.yaml`
- Root `pnpm check` does **not** build the website; extension typecheck excludes `website/` (see `scripts/patch-wxt-tsconfig.mjs`)
- ESLint ignores `website/**`
- Deploy: `.github/workflows/pages.yml` (Node 24, `configure-pages@v5`, `upload-pages-artifact@v5`, `deploy-pages@v5`). Not `ci.yml`.
- **Pages must be enabled** in repo Settings with source **GitHub Actions**, or deploy returns HTTP 404.

## When changing the site

1. `make website-dev` or `make website-preview` to verify layout
2. After editing `src/locales/en/`, run `make website-lint-i18n-fix` then translate; run `make website-lint-i18n` before build
3. User-facing copy: no em dashes (`tabby-prose.mdc`)
4. Add a short **CHANGELOG** bullet only for user-visible marketing changes (not dev-only Makefile tweaks)
5. Update root **README** if URLs or workflow for contributors changed

Stack: Vite, React, TypeScript, `@lottiefiles/dotlottie-web`, `@unhead/react`, `react-i18next`, `vite-plugin-html`.
